Professionals
Partnerships
Careers
Testimonial



Founders

Jason BordainickCo-Founder, Managing Partner
Jason directs and oversees the strategic, operational, and financial areas of the firm.
Jason is the Founder and former CEO of Off Campus Partners (OCP). OCP holds exclusive multi-year agreements with over 70 major universities and facilitates the off-campus housing process through its web-based platform for more than 1.5 million students each year.
In his career, Jason has worked as an investor, mergers & acquisitions professional, and corporate manager, helping to execute over $650M worth of investments and acquisitions on behalf of private investors and corporations.
Jason holds an MBA from Stanford’s Graduate School of Business and a BS in finance from the McIntire School of Commerce at the University of Virginia, where he was honored with the Warwick Johnson Jr. award for academic achievement.
jason@hvpg.com
read more



Andy CavaluzziCo-Founder, Partner
Andrew directs and oversees potential projects from property identification through project development to successful building completion.
Andrew has been involved in real estate brokerage, investment, and development for the past ten years. His diverse background in real estate has provided him with extensive experience to evaluate potential properties and execute successful outcomes.
Andrew cultivates relationships with the municipalities and local residents that are key to the success of any project. His ability to work constructively with local, state and federal government officials on property rehabilitation and acquisitions ensures a positive outcome for local residents, the government, and HVPG investors alike.
Prior to co-founding HVPG, Andrew was a developer leading several real estate rehab, new construction, and development projects as well as a successful entrepreneur in the fitness and hospitality industries.
andrew@hvpg.com
read more



Professionals

Alexandra ColemanBusiness Development Associate



Alex works on all aspects of business development and marketing strategy to further expand HVPG’s acquisition and development pipeline.
Before joining HVPG, Alex worked in business development and client management for a real estate technology company executing both commercial and residential online transactions. She is excited to serve her community through affordable housing preservation and its crucial social impact. Prior to pursuing a career in real estate, Alex spent two years teaching at a bilingual elementary school in Madrid, Spain.
Alex is an MS in Real Estate candidate at the Zicklin School of Business, Baruch College, CUNY. She received her BA in International Studies and Spanish from Middlebury College.
alexandra@hvpg.com


Ryan WithallDevelopment Associate



Ryan contributes to the project development , financial analysis, and asset management of HVPG’s properties.
Before joining HVPG, Ryan spent two years teaching middle school science at The East Harlem School at Exodus House before transitioning to affordable housing, urban planning, and sustainability. Ryan has since worked for the New York City Economic Development Corporation and the nationally recognized real estate and planning consultancy, HR&A Advisors.
Ryan holds an MBA from the Yale School of Management and a Master of Environmental Management from the Yale School of Forestry and Environmental Studies.  He received his BS in Environmental Engineering from Columbia University.
ryan@hvpg.com


Matthew ZulloSenior Associate



Matthew is responsible for acquisition and redevelopment originations. Prior to joining HVPG in July 2012, he was an Asset Manager with a privately held investment group in San Diego focused on commercial real estate. As an advocate for the civic and cultural life of New York, he is an active member of the Municipal Arts Society of New York Urbanist Leadership Council as well as the Business & Professional Committee of the New York City Ballet.
Matthew holds a Master of Science in Real Estate Finance from New York University, a Post-Graduate Diploma in Contemporary Art & Design from the University of Glasgow and Bachelor of Arts in International Affairs & Economics from George Washington University.
matthew@hvpg.com


Partnerships
Hudson Valley & MDG
Hudson Valley – MDG, LLC is a development partnership between Hudson Valley Property Group and MDG Design + Construction, LLC. Hudson Valley – MDG, LLC was formed to develop, acquire, and preserve affordable housing in the Tri-State NY / NJ / CT areas.
MDG and Hudson Valley have an unmatched track record of successfully executing and completing preservation projects. Some highlights include:

6 Tax credit projects in the past 5 years consisting of 610 units in 31 buildings
MDG has been involved in the renovation of over 700 properties comprised of more than 12,500 units of housing totaling over $630 Million
Over 25 years of affordable housing experience
Significant experience in working with local not-for-profits and community groups
Construction partner (MDG) that’s best-in-class in the Northeast with in-place rehabilitation projects
Sample Project by MDG: University Avenue Consolidated Houses
$50 Million Redevelopment
290 Unit Gut Rehabilitation
18 month construction period, substantially completed in 6 months
4% Tax Credits

  
 
 
 
 
Hudson Valley & Royal American
 Hudson Valley & Royal American are working together as partners to develop, acquire, and preserve affordable housing in the Southeastern United States.
Our combined team has deep expertise in the acquisition and redevelopment of affordable housing. Some relevant highlights include:

During the past thirty-five years, more than 112 residential, rental communities have been developed by Royal American Development, Inc.  Ninety-four (94) of these developments, which include over 8,200 residential rental units, are located within the State of Florida.
Royal American Construction (RAC) is a premier construction firm with extensive experience performing tenant-in-place rehabilitations.
In 2014, Hudson Valley – Royal American Development will close on the acquisition of a 100-unit affordable housing property in Florida.

 

Careers
At HVPG, we foster young talent with a competitive and intensive internship program, which can be taken for academic credit. Our interns get to work closely with the principals on deal origination, maintaining relationships, and marketing.
In the past, we have had undergraduate and graduate interns from universities in the New York Metropolitan area such as NYU, Columbia, and CUNY Baruch College. They have gone on to work at notable banks and real estate firms.
If interested in learning more about working at HVPG, please Contact Us
 

Testimonial

“It’s been a wonderful experience working with HVPG. I’ve been given the opportunity to learn so much about affordable housing as well as to take charge in certain projects. The environment is great; everyone really listens to and supports you in your professional development.”Becky Nguyen, Baruch College


“I had a great time interning with Hudson Valley, and it was probably the most rewarding professional experience that I’ve had. Each day brought different challenges and I had the opportunity to make decisions on my own and learn from both my successes and failures. I will always reflect positively on my time at Hudson Valley, and feel that it has made me a more confident young professional.”Klaas Roberts, Columbia Unviersity







