“The Rent is Too Damn High”

Home/Industry News/“The Rent is Too Damn High”







Previous Next 




 


“The Rent is Too Damn High” 
Last week the Joint Center for Housing Studies of Harvard University released their report on Rental Housing in the United States, America’s Rental Housing – Evolving Markets and Needs. The study found, along with many other key facts, that “more than half of renters – 21.1 million households – were cost burdened in 2012, paying more than 30 percent of income for housing. This is the greatest number of housing cost burdened renters on record,” proving, once again, that Jimmy McMillan has a point: “The Rent is Too Damn High.”
 

 
